 <h1 class = "pagetitle">Introduction to the P300 Response</h1>
 <p class = "subtitle">User Tutorial</p>
 <hr class = "sep" />
 <div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content mw-content-ltr" lang="en" dir="ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Since the 1960s, it has been known that presentation of infrequent stimuli evokes a positive deflection in the EEG over parietal cortex about 300 ms after stimulus presentation.
This response has been termed the "P300" or "oddball" potential.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2 id="mw-toc-heading">Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="User_Tutorial%253AIntroduction_to_the_P300_Response.html#Behavioral_Properties"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Behavioral Properties</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="User_Tutorial%253AIntroduction_to_the_P300_Response.html#Physical_Properties"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Physical Properties</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-3"><a href="User_Tutorial%253AIntroduction_to_the_P300_Response.html#BCI_Construction"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">BCI Construction</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-4"><a href="User_Tutorial%253AIntroduction_to_the_P300_Response.html#Next_Step"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">Next Step</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-5"><a href="User_Tutorial%253AIntroduction_to_the_P300_Response.html#See_also"><span class="tocnumber">5</span> <span class="toctext">See also</span></a></li>
